        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 5:48PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Weldona, or 18 miles northwest of Fort Morgan, moving
north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Raymer, Antelope Springs, Stoneham, Keota, Jackson Reservoir
and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
